channel.title: How do you extract the funorb cache(s)?
channel.description:
How would you go about extracting the files from the funorb cache? Not sure if defyboy's extractor would work for this, because I'm getting some errors. These are the rules (I've tried a few others similar to this) that I used for ace of skies:
[code=java] input=C:\.jagex_cache_32\aceofskies\ output=F:\Jagex\Funorb\Cache\aceofskies\ version=1 data=main_file_cache.dat0,14 index=main_file_cache.idx0,cache0,dat index=main_file_cache.idx1,cache1,dat index=main_file_cache.idx2,cache2,dat index=main_file_cache.idx3,cache3,dat index=main_file_cache.idx4,cache4,dat index=main_file_cache.idx5,cache5,dat index=main_file_cache.idx6,cache6,dat index=main_file_cache.idx7,cache7,dat index=main_file_cache.idx8,cache8,dat index=main_file_cache.idx9,cache9,dat index=main_file_cache.idx10,cache10,dat index=main_file_cache.idx11,cache11,dat index=main_file_cache.idx12,cache12,dat index=main_file_cache.idx255,cache255,dat [/code]
Am I doing something wrong here? Or is there another extractor that would work?
Edit: And to some: I don't need you to tell me that you don't care about anything funorb related :P I know that already.
PS: When I try arcanists, halfway through I get a "PANIC! RANDOMISED BLOCK!" :|
